snippet: Omar Suleiman, former President Hosni Mubarak’s intelligence chief and vice president, filed to run for president in Egypt, but his entry is unlikely to shake up the race.
abstract: Omar Suleiman, intelligence chief and vice president under former Egyptian president Hosni Mubarak, files papers in Egypt declaring himself a presidential candidate; his formal entry gives Egyptians a chance to cast a vote against the revolution and for the old order, though many say that he is unlikely to shake up the race.
lead_paragraph: Omar Suleiman, former President Hosni Mubarak’s intelligence chief and vice president, filed to run for president in Egypt, but his entry is unlikely to shake up the race.

headline.seo: Omar Suleiman, Egypt’s New Candidate, Represents Old Order
headline.main: Egyptian Presidential Candidate Carries Banner of the Old Order
headline.print_headline: Egyptian Presidential Candidate Carries Banner of the Old Order
